# 1. Course Description

Artificial Intelligence has become an integral component of modern cybersecurity systems by enabling automated threat detection, intelligent malware analysis, phishing identification, intrusion detection, security analytics, and incident response. Traditional signature-based security mechanisms struggle against sophisticated and rapidly evolving cyber threats, creating the need for intelligent systems capable of learning from security data.

This course introduces students to the integration of Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, and Deep Learning with cybersecurity. Students learn cybersecurity fundamentals before progressing to AI-based solutions for threat detection, malware classification, network traffic analysis, explainable AI, adversarial machine learning, and responsible AI. The course emphasizes practical implementation through demonstrations, laboratory exercises, and a semester mini-project using publicly available cybersecurity datasets.

