# 5. Pedagogy & Teaching Methods

The course follows an Outcome-Based Education (OBE) approach emphasizing conceptual understanding, practical implementation, and problem-solving through AI-enabled cybersecurity applications.

## Teaching Strategies

- Interactive lectures
- Demonstration-based learning
- Problem-based learning
- Project-based learning
- Case-study discussions
- Collaborative learning
- Flipped classroom
- Industry-oriented seminars
- Continuous formative assessment

## Merrill's First Principles

| Principle | Implementation |
|---|---|
| Problem-Centered | Every unit begins with a real cybersecurity problem. |
| Activation | Prior knowledge of networking, Python and AI is recalled. |
| Demonstration | Faculty demonstrates AI models and cybersecurity tools. |
| Application | Students implement ML/DL models on security datasets. |
| Integration | Students present, defend and improve AI-based cyber defence solutions. |

